So I became a Real Estate student and entrepreneur over 6 months ago 🤓. To be honest, I thought Real Estate was boring and stupid but that was only because I knew nothing about it.

I used to think there was only one way of buying real estate, which is the traditional way everyone knows or that becoming an investor required a lot of money and was very complicated.

Turned out after so much study and research that’s not the case, this world is huge and there are so many ways to enter and make money in real estate that most people have no idea about.

It’s simply shocking, how little the public or even well known real estate entrepreneurs and business people don’t know about.

There are so many opportunities out there, however being an entrepreneur at anything is not easy at all, it requires investing in the right mentors and education, opening your mind to new ideas and ways of doing business, it requires a lot of discipline and determination, having a vision bigger than yourself, networking and partnering with other people, and whats most important, having a focused long term mindset because of everything we do today we’ll not see major results until the next 5 to 10 years, yet most people prefer to settle and trade their dreams for short term gratification.

Anyways, I won’t tell you much but if you want to take your mindset and knowledge to the next level I suggest you take a look to this book “Wealth Without Cash” from one of my mentors @pacemorby , it will blow out your mind and will make you realize there is so much out there still to learn. ✌🏻

Also, I wanted to say that I am very grateful because even though I recently went through very dark times that no one knew about, I found new mentors, friends and partners that supported me in this new journey and make my life so much fun, fulfilling and worthy, thank you so much guys @raymondsubtoco  @garrett_groener 🙏

I recently joined Toastmasters because I wanted to challenge myself to overcome my fears, anxiety and limiting beliefs by improving my communication skills, specially in public speaking. 💙

It’s crazy I had no idea that this existed and I found about it just while reading a book 📚🤷🏼‍♀️.

Toastmasters international is a nonprofit educational organization that teaches public speaking and leadership skills through a worldwide network of clubs. Super affordable to join!

I joined @coralgablestm which is one my local clubs, founded since 1955. And really, I can’t believe I just found out, it’s been running for quite some time.

The 1st project is named the Ice Breaker and this week I had the honor to give my first speech which awarded the best speaker of the night 🥹💙. So proud of myself, preparing it was not easy!

I’m so happy about this new step in my personal development, I hope to grow and inspire others to do the same. 

If you feel like you need help with your communication skills, overcoming fears of speaking in front of people, or career growth, then make sure to search for your local club and also let others know about it. I believe organizations this like deserve more promotion. It’s such a beautiful and safe space with amazing supporting people.

Getting out of your comfort zone can you change your life! Never stop working on yourself and be sure to acquire new skills as much as possible. 

We can always change, we can always improve, we can always achieve better just 1% a day. 🔥

Today, I completed a full 24hr fast for the 1st time ever!! 🥳 I feel so accomplished because I thought this was impossible, but once again I am overcoming the limits of my mind for a higher purpose: the wellness of my body. 💙

There is a lot of scientific research that supports the benefits of fasting. Even many religions or spiritual practices make it part of their traditions to reach higher levels of consciousness.

All we are doing is mimicking the lifestyle of our prehistoric ancestors. Our bodies are designed to go without food for long periods of time. By doing this we allow our bodies to heal and repair themselves. 

Something important to note is that women need to fast differently than men. We need to fast according to our individual menstrual cycles. 🙋‍♀️

After 17 hours we reach a phase named Autophagy, when the body gets rid of viruses, bacterias, and dysfunctional cells (like cancer) and recicle them to be used as fuel.

After 24 hours the body gets a whole intestinal stem cells reboot building a better microbiome which is the base of our metabolism and immune system.

The longer you go better results…. 
You lose fat, sharper mind, less anxiety, less bad food cravings and more.

I really encourage you to try it, but make sure to educate yourself on the topic before starting. 
Follow @dr.mindypelz , a leading expert I highly recommend to learn from! 🙌🏻

Running or jogging in the sand requires a lot more effort, extra energy and muscle engagement, therefore it’s a great resistance and strength training. It also causes less impact on your joints versus running on a regular hard surface. Start by walking and jogging in intervals for 20-30 mins, 2 or 3 times a week, then you can add a little more as you feel more comfortable. It’s also a great meditation. Enjoy the views, the music and the fresh air 💙
